                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.4612/170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. Reference your 485, June 17, 7 p.m. Inform Consul at Harbin that the
                    Department wishes to make no formal request for the seals and to conduct no
                    correspondence with the Chinese authorities regarding police action through
                    which they were obtained. The Department would be pleased to have the Consul get
                    possession of the seals or to convince himself of their destruction, provided he
                    could accomplish either end without written request or formalities and without
                    indication that he was acting under instructions.<note n="72" xml:id="d89fn72"
                        >In reply, the Consul at Harbin reported that the seals and other materials
                        seized by the Chinese had been forwarded to Mukden headquarters
                        (125.4612/171).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
